cervical.textareatext: Normal lordotic curve, no scoliosis, swelling/edema or scars.

cervical.label: Cervical Ranges of Motion Table A-2 page 597: AMA Estimated Normal: Flexion (50D), Extension (60D), Lateral Bend (Right and Left) (45D), Rotation (Right and Left) (80D). Motion is reported right over left side in Degrees (D). Measurements are obtained with an inclinometer (two location method).
cervical.textareatext: Enter three consecutive true spinal angle measurements (Top spinal segment reading (DЩ lower spinal segment reading (D); Example: Calvarium flexion 60 DРT1 flexion 17D = Flexion true spinal angle measurement 43 D). Cervical flexion plane measurements are valid if they are measured within 5D or 10%. Cervical lateral bending and rotation plane measurements are valid if they are measured within 5D or 10% of the set mean (whichever is greater). A maximum of six measurement attempts may be performed.

cervical.label: Actual inclinometer measurements of the range of motion are only required for PR-4 (Permanent & Stationary) reports. Visual estimates of the range of motion may be adequate for Doctor's First reports and PR-2 reports.
